.TH "snd_soc_register_dai" 9 "snd_soc_register_dai" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_soc_register_dai \- Register a DAI dynamically & create its widgets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct snd_soc_dai *" snd_soc_register_dai
.BI "(struct snd_soc_component *component "  ","
.BI "struct snd_soc_dai_driver *dai_drv "  ","
.BI "bool legacy_dai_naming "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "component" 12
The component the DAIs are registered for
.IP "dai_drv" 12
DAI driver to use for the DAI
.IP "legacy_dai_naming" 12
if true, use legacy single-name format;
if false, use multiple-name format;
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Topology can use this API to register DAIs when probing a component.
These DAIs's widgets will be freed in the card cleanup and the DAIs
will be freed in the component cleanup.
